the United States is unique in having the best universities in the world, so there are these

25:59.680 --> 26:09.120
privileged spots that are excellent, uniquely excellent. So when you look at the comparison,

26:09.200 --> 26:19.040
education in China is improving rapidly, and the quantity is a quantity of educated people

26:19.040 --> 26:25.200
in the areas that they're moving in are, is greater, and the resources that they're putting

26:25.200 --> 26:33.680
behind it is greater, and so you see the results are greater. But it's sort of a long line that

26:33.680 --> 26:42.000
I'm dealing with. If you were to follow through in terms of actual productions, I think you know

26:42.000 --> 26:49.440
in terms of technologies, there are some areas that the United States is in a lead. At the moment,

26:49.440 --> 26:55.680
there's some areas that China's in a lead, but China's gaining very quickly. When I first went

26:55.760 --> 27:04.880
to China, 1984, I would bring $10 calculators, and I gave them away as gifts to high-ranking people,

27:04.880 --> 27:13.200
and they thought they were miracle devices. Right now, in terms of areas like quantum computing,

27:13.200 --> 27:23.120
and AI, and you know, many areas, you have a race going on, and so if you take the trajectory

27:23.120 --> 27:28.480
of the competitiveness, not just look at the current level, you have a situation where they're

27:28.480 --> 27:34.720
improving at a much faster rate. This is all good for the world if the world can get along.

27:36.560 --> 27:44.960
And the main thing I think is, in just how do you have a healthy world, and how do you have a

27:44.960 --> 27:51.280
strong economy, and how do you have a strong situation, is be strong. The United States's

27:51.280 --> 27:57.120
war is with itself. That's the main war. You know, it's very simple in history.

27:59.440 --> 28:08.880
Be financially sound, earn more than you spend, and be strong in these ways, and pretty much

28:08.880 --> 28:14.960
everything will take care of itself. But you make it sound simple, of course,

28:14.960 --> 28:20.240
because there's a momentum when things degrade. When the education system degrades, when you

28:20.240 --> 28:25.600
start borrowing, when, I mean, all of these indicators, once they start going down,

28:26.800 --> 28:30.080
there's a momentum to it, right? So it's hard to reverse it.

28:30.080 --> 28:35.840
Right, and there are circumstances that you're then in. For example, indebtedness,

28:36.880 --> 28:45.520
you know, it's politically desirable for those to borrow money and spend, because their

28:45.520 --> 28:51.840
constituencies only look at what they get. And when they get a lot, they don't pay attention

28:51.840 --> 28:58.000
to the balance sheet and how much debt is on the books. So it's always better to borrow, spend,

28:58.560 --> 29:06.160
and then leave the cleanup to the next guy. And so you inherit a lot. You inherit it as

