a new president enters in, or new legislators. They have a lot of debt. They have a broken down

29:15.040 --> 29:23.440
infrastructure. They don't have enough money to fix that. And so that's the lay of the land that

29:24.160 --> 29:32.320
the prior generations put you in, and there you are. And so that's right. It's difficult,

29:32.320 --> 29:37.840
because when you start to think, okay, what's healthy? Well, spend, earn more than you spend.

29:37.840 --> 29:43.840
Well, that's not so easy, because, you know, what does that mean? Go earn more? I mean,

29:43.840 --> 29:50.960
okay, that's not so easy. Spend less? That isn't going to work. So now what do you do? Okay,

29:50.960 --> 29:56.800
you have this debt that you then monetize, and that's why it's classic. So yes, that's why these

29:56.800 --> 30:03.360
cycles occur, because what has created before, what happened before created the lay of the land

30:03.360 --> 30:09.120
that is then increasingly difficult to deal with. So what can great leaders do in this moment? I mean,

30:09.200 --> 30:16.320
maybe my sense is leadership is crucial here. So for example, to do very large projects that

30:16.320 --> 30:24.080
invest in the education system, that sort of try to fix the fundamentals, or maybe invest more and

30:24.080 --> 30:30.320
more into the innovation and the development of new technologies and so on. It feels like that

30:30.320 --> 30:37.840
just doesn't happen organically. So you have to have strong leaders that

30:39.280 --> 30:42.480
convince the populace of the importance of these ideas.

