Well, I completely agree with your list. What we have is a situation where everybody

30:50.400 --> 30:56.000
has their opinions, and they have to sort of get them exactly right, and they all fight with

30:56.080 --> 31:03.440
each other about whether their opinions. So the most important thing is that we become bipartisan

31:03.440 --> 31:11.280
so that we don't, and we get over our differences. I would have a bipartisan cabinet. I would draw upon

31:12.960 --> 31:19.120
both members of both parties, the moderates, who are going to be able to work together.

31:19.840 --> 31:29.200
So as then we have one country, and then we deal with those in a means that works for the majority

31:29.200 --> 31:36.160
of the people in the middle, rather than the polarity. I think our greatest risk is in not

31:36.160 --> 31:44.080
being able to do that. So I would say that's a paramount importance because we have the resources,

31:44.720 --> 31:51.680
wealth, real wealth, and science, and everything has never been better than it is.

31:52.400 --> 31:58.720
But the notion is that it has to work for the majority of people, and we have to keep it

31:58.720 --> 32:07.440
being productive. So that group has got to calmly and knowledgeably work together so that they

32:07.440 --> 32:14.000
increase the size of the pie, and they create broad-based prosperity. So that is a paramount

32:14.000 --> 32:22.240
importance. Whatever they do, if they do it that way, I can say I'm happy about because that other

32:22.240 --> 32:33.920
alternative is the really scary alternative. The scary alternative, the different ways it has

32:33.920 --> 32:41.840
evolved throughout history, some of it has led to wars. What are the future trajectories that

32:41.840 --> 32:48.160
lead to a potential war with China? Cold war or hot war? Is this something you think about?

32:48.160 --> 32:52.960
Is this something you're worried about? Yeah, I'd like to talk about both wars. So the war

32:52.960 --> 33:00.240
with China, as I say, there are five kinds of wars. There's a trade war technology war,

33:00.960 --> 33:10.640
geopolitical influence war, capital war, and military war. As far as military war goes,

33:10.640 --> 33:18.160
I think it's only a Taiwan issue, but that's a big issue, and we could talk about that for a minute.

33:18.720 --> 33:26.720
But those others, they'll be rough competitions, and we'll have that type of evolution over a

33:26.720 --> 33:33.840
period of time. That's what that war looks like. Taiwan has been, for a long time,

33:35.920 --> 33:45.760
a sovereignty issue to China, and it has its roots in what's called 100 years of humiliation.

33:47.120 --> 33:55.600
From the 1840s to 1949, foreign powers came in, took advantage of China. They had the Opium

33:55.600 --> 34:06.880
Wars in such times, and that represented the 100 years of humiliation. Taiwan represents

34:06.880 --> 34:14.480
their sovereignty and their important thing. And 50 years ago, starting 50 years ago,

34:14.480 --> 34:23.600
there was an agreement that there is one China, and Taiwan is part of China, and that there would be

34:24.240 --> 34:32.160
peaceful reunification. The peaceful reunification hasn't happened, and in their view,

34:33.200 --> 34:39.680
that's a very big issue. And so it's a big contentious issue, and that could produce a

34:39.680 --> 34:46.960
military war, could produce a military accident, it's a very tense situation. And if we had a

34:46.960 --> 34:55.680
military war, God help us because of the capacity in all different new ways to inflict harm on each

34:55.680 --> 35:03.360
other. But anyway, that's that. If you don't have that military war, you'll have the competition

35:03.360 --> 35:10.320
between those other kinds of wars, and whoever is strongest in those areas will win.

35:11.280 --> 35:13.840
Where do you put cyber war within the five?

35:14.560 --> 35:21.040
Well, cyber war is a military war. I'm assuming the type of cyber war that you're

35:21.040 --> 35:27.920
referring to is that which it's used to inflict pain on the other party through cyber. So cyber wars,

35:27.920 --> 35:34.000
you'll see cyber war, you could see space war, you can see drone warfare,

35:34.720 --> 35:41.920
you, new types of warfare, not just the traditional and nuclear type of warfare,

35:42.480 --> 35:43.920
but you could see any of the above.

35:46.000 --> 35:50.560
What are the defining characteristics? What are the interesting things about

35:50.560 --> 35:54.880
Xi Jinping, the president of China, as a leader on the world stage?

35:55.760 --> 36:03.760
His father was a early leader. He was himself

36:06.640 --> 36:15.600
in the Cultural Revolution in times, treated brutally. And during that period of time,

36:15.680 --> 36:24.880
it was very, very difficult. And he came up through the ranks and is a very intelligent man.

36:26.480 --> 36:33.760
When he first came to power, as you know, they have two five-year terms, and we're now coming to

36:33.760 --> 36:40.240
the end of the second of those five-year terms. When he first came to power, he felt that there

36:40.240 --> 36:48.560
should be a lot of reform, and reform meant moving to much more of a market and open economy.

36:49.360 --> 36:57.520
When that happened in him coming in, I had some contact with economic policymakers, but in the

36:57.520 --> 37:05.120
circumstances then, were that five major banks lent to state-owned enterprises and local governments

37:05.120 --> 37:12.080
with implied government guarantees. And so there was not control of that and the movement to aim

37:12.080 --> 37:19.200
more of a market economy. And the development of markets was a primary. And also the dealing

37:19.200 --> 37:25.280
with the corruption issue. There was a lot of corruption prior to that, and that was viewed

37:25.280 --> 37:33.680
as an existential threat to the system. So that became the primary objective. And then as time

37:33.680 --> 37:42.800
progressed over those 10 years, there was a lot of changing in the world, their financial

37:42.800 --> 37:49.120
circumstances, opening many, many other markets. They particularly getting money to small and

37:49.120 --> 37:55.280
medium-sized enterprises and developing a lending system and then establishing controls on it.

37:55.280 --> 38:07.760
So right now, there's a vibrant capital markets. You can raise capital, you can be an entrepreneur,

38:07.760 --> 38:13.840
you can become a billionaire in the capital markets. And they developed the markets to be

38:13.840 --> 38:22.560
the second largest capital markets. At the same time, they had to deal with their rising debt issue,

38:22.560 --> 38:32.640
which they began to deal with really about four years ago, when the second term began.

38:35.360 --> 38:46.800
And then Lou Ha became the vice premier responsible for that and to deal with those issues. So

38:46.880 --> 38:53.040
you see right now that what's happening is the dealing with the real estate bubble.

38:53.040 --> 38:59.360
There was a development in real estate, a bubble, which produced a lot of unproductive lending.

39:00.000 --> 39:09.840
And Xi Jinping said, houses are meant to live in, not to speculate on. And so that was wasteful.

39:09.840 --> 39:14.800
So they established what they call three red lines, which are financial ratios,

39:14.800 --> 39:22.080
that the property developers had to live within. And that is then causing the adjustments that are

39:22.080 --> 39:29.360
going on now, which in my view are very healthy because whenever there's bankruptcies and so on,

39:29.360 --> 39:35.200
the most in the public think, okay, that's a problem. It's in many cases really a cleaning

39:35.200 --> 39:42.560
up of bad debts and bad practices. And so that's what's going on. So that's, let's say economically.

39:42.560 --> 39:49.920
At the same time, there is the changing relationships, the changing world order,

39:49.920 --> 39:55.280
the changing relationships with the United States and other countries, which is becoming

39:56.080 --> 40:04.240
much less cooperative and much more warlike, much more confrontational. Those two things,

40:04.240 --> 40:12.000
the domestic debt problem and the domestic has led to what's called core, what they call core

40:12.000 --> 40:22.080
leadership, which means a leadership more around him that is less challenging because they believe

40:22.080 --> 40:29.760
in history that during very difficult times, a more centrally controlled decision making process

40:29.760 --> 40:36.400
lends itself better than to a more fragmented political contentious project. And that's basically

40:36.400 --> 40:46.480
what's going on now. You said it very eloquently, but you mean the leadership is surrounded by yes men

40:46.480 --> 40:55.360
and there's a lot of centralized control. That characterization is much more black and white

40:55.360 --> 40:59.520
than it really is. But it leans towards that direction.

41:00.320 --> 41:05.280
Like, for example, of the standing members of the Politburo, four are more alleged,

41:05.280 --> 41:12.560
allowed him, three are less so. You have to understand that it's kind of a collective

41:12.560 --> 41:19.120
leadership at the top. And then, of course, there's just jockeying for power in a highly

41:19.120 --> 41:29.280
political sense at the top. But no one leader can be successful against all those powers at

41:29.280 --> 41:36.800
the top. So it's very politically negotiating. It's very much more like, if you put in the

41:36.800 --> 41:41.360
United States, the Democrats and the Republicans, and they had to be in the same government and

41:41.360 --> 41:47.840
they work it out, it's kind of something like that. And so that's that struggle, but it's an

41:47.840 --> 41:53.760
internal struggle. Where do you put the importance of some of these ideas at the founding of the

41:53.760 --> 41:59.920
United States when then, now we're talking about that at the context of China, the freedom of

41:59.920 --> 42:05.920
speech freedoms. What China is doing with the central management of a lot of things, it's

42:05.920 --> 42:13.840
enabling a lot of growth, but it's also limiting people on the very basic level in terms of freedom,

42:13.840 --> 42:19.600
the kind of freedom that I think can lead to entrepreneurship, to starting new businesses,

42:19.600 --> 42:24.480
to having big dreams and chasing those dreams, and then creating totally new things in whatever

42:24.480 --> 42:32.480
the space, maybe in technology, in business and whatever. How important is that as a metric for

42:32.480 --> 42:40.320
society? Well, they have a view which is the idea of a dialectic, which means that two things are

42:41.280 --> 42:48.080
that everything comes with pros and cons, and two opposites exist. And you want the benefits of

42:48.080 --> 42:55.600
those two opposites, and how do you deal with the benefits of those two opposites? So let's say

42:55.600 --> 43:02.160
you want the capital markets because it gets money into the hands of the entrepreneurs who are

43:02.160 --> 43:09.120
motivated, they build fortunes, and that drives an economy to do very well. And at the same time,

43:09.120 --> 43:16.800
it produces the other problems, the wealth gaps, the other problems, then the debt cycle that we're

43:16.800 --> 43:26.000
talking about and so on. And Deng Xiaoping, how do you reconcile communism and the market economy

43:26.000 --> 43:33.680
and the capital markets? And he famously said, and it doesn't matter if it's a white cat or a

43:33.680 --> 43:39.920
black cat, just as long as it catches mice. In other words, if it works in making the country richer,

43:40.560 --> 43:45.200
then that becomes the objective, and then they move that along. So there are these conflicts,

43:46.480 --> 43:53.840
and one of the leaders described it to me as follows, because it's confusion and it goes back

43:53.840 --> 44:01.200
over a period of time. There's a hierarchy, and it's an extension of the family he described it.

44:01.200 --> 44:08.000
And he said, the United States is a country of individuals and individualism,

44:09.600 --> 44:18.560
and that is its vibrancy that we see. The individual rights to speak up, the individual

44:20.800 --> 44:24.880
protection of the individual, individual property rights, and all of those things

44:25.440 --> 44:31.360
is of paramount importance. And we build our organization. That's why democracy is from the

44:31.360 --> 44:37.680
bottom up, or even a company will get together and we'll be partners to prosper together. That

44:37.680 --> 44:46.240
is the American approach. He was describing that in China, it's an extension of the Confucian family,

44:46.720 --> 44:54.800
essentially. And so it's almost like there's a hierarchy. And so what they think about is

44:54.800 --> 45:02.320
the common good, not the individualism. So for example, if they want a high-speed rail to go

45:02.320 --> 45:08.880
from one place to another, and that's best in the common good, then the individual protections that

45:08.880 --> 45:17.120
would stand in the way of doing that would be of secondary concern. So that notion of controlling.

45:17.120 --> 45:28.160
So for example, what they're doing with video games, they control what type of video games

45:28.160 --> 45:37.200
and how many hours a day kids can be on video games operating in that way, because they believe

45:37.280 --> 45:43.120
that that's good for the society and that's very controlling. In the United States, I think probably

45:43.120 --> 45:48.960
most parents would say, leave it to me, and it's a matter between me and my kids. The same thing

45:48.960 --> 45:56.080
has to do with data. In other words, in the United States, who controls the data? Does the company

45:56.080 --> 46:02.960
control the data? Do you individually control the data? And so the inclination would be to figure

46:02.960 --> 46:08.080
that out, but nobody would say that the government is going to control the data because of our

46:08.080 --> 46:14.320
inclination of really anti-government control. In China, it would be that the government will

46:14.320 --> 46:20.240
control the data because that's going to be best for the society and it depends who you trust.

46:21.520 --> 46:31.120
So that difference in philosophy is very much at the heart of that. As far as your question in terms

46:31.120 --> 46:39.120
of effectiveness, it really is, in China's case, it's how you balance the things. So what they're

46:39.120 --> 46:48.000
attempting to do is to create a lot of freedom and creativity in areas that are not political, let's

46:48.000 --> 46:56.640
say. And so you see a lot of entrepreneurship, you see a lot of product development, you see a lot

46:56.640 --> 47:04.880
of creativity happening in that way. So the stereotype that you don't see creativity happening

47:04.880 --> 47:10.880
is an old stereotype. There's a lot of creativity certainly happening and the system can work well

47:10.880 --> 47:16.720
if they can achieve that kind of balance. It's proven to work well. Since I started going there

47:16.720 --> 47:28.160
in 1984, real per capita income has increased by 26 times. The longevity rate has increased by 10

47:28.160 --> 47:36.400
years. The poverty rate has fallen from 88% to less than 1% in terms of basics like starvation

47:36.400 --> 47:44.480
and things. And if you read history, Plato's Republic, he talks about the cycles, democracy

47:45.120 --> 47:53.360
and autocratic and the benevolent despot and all of that. Each has their own vulnerability. The

47:53.360 --> 47:59.920
vulnerability of democracy, which has been a remarkable, remarkable system and I don't have

47:59.920 --> 48:10.480
to extol the benefits of it. But the vulnerability of it has always been the internal conflict that

48:10.480 --> 48:21.680
produces itself as anarchy. In World War II, four democracies chose to be autocracies

48:22.960 --> 48:30.080
because there was internal disorder and there was the belief will somebody bring about order

48:30.080 --> 48:37.120
and get control of the situation. That was in Germany, Italy, Japan and Spain.

48:37.840 --> 48:45.360
They were parliamentary systems that turned themselves over to that. So, both systems

48:46.240 --> 48:54.720
have vulnerabilities. I think the main thing that we need to think about is those vulnerabilities.

48:54.720 --> 49:03.360
Democracy is an amazing system because the adherence to the rules and the system

49:03.360 --> 49:09.440
and the checks and balances is quite amazing and it gives it a flexibility to change without

49:09.440 --> 49:16.960
civil wars. But there has to be the respect of the rules. And when you see something like

49:18.240 --> 49:27.840
they will not accept elections or they will not accept rules, history has shown when the causes

49:27.920 --> 49:34.400
that people are behind are more important to them than the system. The system is in jeopardy.

49:34.400 --> 49:41.760
So, we have a situation that's very much like that in terms of, let's say, the 2024 elections.

49:42.480 --> 49:51.280
I believe that there's a very high chance that neither side will accept losing, for example.

49:51.760 --> 50:00.240
And so, we have that kind of a situation. So, one would hope that one could rise above the

50:00.240 --> 50:09.200
disagreements and rely on the system for resolving disagreements because if that doesn't happen,

50:09.200 --> 50:16.160
then we have our own chaos. So, the kind of the trend that started in 2020,

50:16.720 --> 50:24.960
or I suppose it's been growing. One representation of this internal disorder has been

50:24.960 --> 50:28.880
the growing trend of being skeptical about the results of the election.

50:29.520 --> 50:33.920
Well, it started before that. There was the emergence of population

50:35.040 --> 50:43.680
before President Trump was elected. He was basically elected as a populist because there

50:43.680 --> 50:50.000
was a large percentage of the population that felt that the system didn't work for them,

50:50.560 --> 50:57.600
and he tapped into that, and he was largely elected as a populist leader, first populist leader

50:57.600 --> 51:06.880
in a developed country. And so, populism began then, and that was a battle of one group against

51:06.960 --> 51:13.280
the other group. And so, since then, it's been like that, and it continued to grow.

51:17.920 --> 51:24.720
You've mentioned the vulnerability of democracy, the internal disorder is the

51:24.720 --> 51:30.400
vulnerability of democracy. What's the vulnerability of a system like China? Maybe one way to

51:30.960 --> 51:34.880
say is put China aside and look at history, look at Soviet Union.

51:34.880 --> 51:38.960
What's the vulnerability of a communist-type system?

51:39.840 --> 51:48.960
Well, I'll call it both communist and autocratic, depending on how much autocracy,

51:48.960 --> 51:58.720
is that it lacks flexibility. It lacks the ability, but I should deal with them differently.

51:59.440 --> 52:05.600
In other words, there's the economic system. The economic system threatens motivation

52:06.160 --> 52:15.440
and productivity. So, communism or socialism has to be done in a way where you can threaten

52:15.440 --> 52:24.000
productivity. Capitalism has, and what I mean by that, I mean free markets and capital markets.

52:24.640 --> 52:32.480
I've been an effective way of allocating resources and also creating the incentives

52:32.480 --> 52:38.400
and the resources, providing the resources for the inventiveness of new ideas. And so,

52:38.400 --> 52:46.000
if I compare that, what the Chinese have done, to a large extent, is to recognize that and have made

52:46.000 --> 52:53.920
a move, that's why the seeming dialectic or the conflict between those two things exist. But

52:53.920 --> 53:03.360
anyway, that's it. As far as an autocratic system, rather than one man, one vote from the population

53:03.360 --> 53:11.040
up, the risks of the autocratic system is that there's enough discontent that arises,

53:12.000 --> 53:20.080
that the system doesn't have the flexibility, and that rather than bending, it breaks.

53:21.360 --> 53:29.440
That's the big risk. The notion of trying to control a population, if there's that, rather

53:29.440 --> 53:36.000
than giving it the flexibility. So, that would be the big risk of the autocratic system.

53:36.080 --> 53:41.120
What's the human, because you mentioned like the top gets bigger with the empires,

53:42.400 --> 53:49.600
and you start taking things for granted, is some of this just human nature. So, the concern with

53:49.600 --> 54:00.400
China, with autocratic nations, the concern with the Third Reich, the Soviet Union, was that

54:01.360 --> 54:07.600
fundamentally, at the individual level, the humans involved at the top, they start becoming,

54:07.600 --> 54:13.920
they're starting to lose touch with the reality, in a way that no longer makes them. I guess that's

54:13.920 --> 54:19.120
the representation of the flexibility that you're referring to. Well, I mean, in a democracy,

54:20.320 --> 54:25.680
you could change. You can go as far left or as far right. You can change the leaders easily,

54:25.680 --> 54:30.800
and so the people don't become, they pretty much only have themselves to blame.

54:33.920 --> 54:41.440
One of the problems of that is they may not choose the best leaders, but they have that

54:41.440 --> 54:48.960
flexibility. So, vote and you get what you wanted. In the case of the autocratic, let's say, leaders,

54:48.960 --> 54:57.360
and then the movement from democracies to autocracies, what you see normally, that movement,

54:57.360 --> 55:03.360
is that one of the systems is not working. Let's say the democracy is not effectively. Everybody's

55:03.360 --> 55:08.080
arguing with each other, and nobody's getting anything done, and you know, like Mussolini,

55:08.080 --> 55:13.840
the trains are not running on time, and that would be the example. Geez, this place has gotten

